T.I. has grown to truly be one of his generation&#039;s most captivating speakers. 
Whether he&#039;s conversing frankly with a room full of youth about the positive 
side of staying in school and following their dreams, or moving tens of 
thousands at one of his concerts, the audiences are immediately engrossed 
by the King of the South&#039;s words. T.I., here delivers his most potent and 
important LP to date; &#039;Paper Trail.&#039; The title is a direct reference to T.I.&#039;s 
return to literally writing down his lyrics- a practice he hasnt engaged in since 
his debut. By going back to the basics T.I. has evolved into a better MC. The 
album features guest appearances and production by Lil Wayne. Rihanna, 
Usher, The Dream, Fall Out Boy, Kanye West, B.O.B, John Legend, DJ 
Toomp, Swizz Beatz, Drumma Boy, & Danja. This is the explicit version.
